<db:titleabbrev>Qt Multimedia Documentation</db:titleabbrev>
<db:abstract>
<db:para>An essential module which provides multimedia-related widgets.</db:para>
</db:abstract>
<db:pubdate>2024-12-27</db:pubdate>
<db:date>2024-12-27</db:date>
<db:authorgroup>
<db:author>
<db:orgname class="corporation">The Qt Company Ltd.</db:orgname>
</db:author>
</db:authorgroup>
</db:info>
<db:para>Qt Multimedia Widgets provides additional multimedia-related widgets and controls. The classes expand the capabilities of the <db:link xlink:href="qtmultimedia-index.xml">Qt Multimedia</db:link> and <db:link xlink:href="qtwidgets-index.xml">Qt Widgets</db:link> modules.</db:para>
<db:section xml:id="getting-started">
<db:title>Getting Started</db:title>
<db:para>To enable Qt Multimedia Widgets in a project, add this directive into the C++ files:</db:para>
<db:programlisting language="cpp">#include &amp;lt;QtMultimediaWidgets&amp;gt;
</db:programlisting>
<db:para>To link against the C++ libraries, add the following to your <db:code>qmake</db:code> project file:</db:para>
<db:programlisting language="cpp">QT += multimediawidgets
</db:programlisting>
</db:section>
